<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,151,751]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,548,572]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named in honor of Lewis L. Deitz, retired Professor, Department of Entomology, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,384,583,607]" country="United States of America" name="North Carolina" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">North Carolina State</collectingRegion>
University, Raleigh, for his outstanding teaching and fine research on the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[1233,1387,583,607]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Membracidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1825" box="[151,294,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cicadellidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,151,751]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,656,680]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
From 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nielson, 1986 e: 762)" baseAuthorityName="Nielson" baseAuthorityPageNumber="762" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[388,783,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Docalidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paracrista">
<emphasis box="[388,408,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[422,554,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">paracrista (</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nielson" box="[555,774,655,679]" firstAuthor="Nielson" page="762" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="749 - 762" refId="ref55458" refString="Nielson, M. W. (1986 e) New South American leafhoppers in the genus Docalidia with a key to 37 species (Cidadellidae: Coelidiinae: Teruliini). Great Basin Naturalist, 46 (4), 749 - 762." type="journal article" year="1986" yearSuffix="e">Nielson, 1986e:762</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
to which it is nearest, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="2011" box="[1032,1127,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Docalidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deitzi">
<emphasis box="[1032,1127,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">D. deitzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the very large apical 1/3 of the stylar apophysis in dorsal view, by the more distal position of the aedeagal spine and by the presence of preatrial lateral lobes on the aedeagus in ventral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
